definition.value: Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of the beta-ketopyranosidic linkages of 3-deoxy-D-manno-2-octulosonate in capsular polysaccharides.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-6) linkages between alpha-L-fucose and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine in glycopeptides such as immunoglobulin G glycopeptide and fucosyl-asialo-agalacto-fetuin.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-D-(1--gt-2)-(4-O-methyl)glucuronosyl links in the main chain of hardwood xylans.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-xylosyl links in some glucuronoarabinoxylans.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-2)-alpha-D- and (1--gt-6)-alpha-D- linkages in mannan, releasing D-mannose.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-(1--gt-4)-D-glucosidic linkage in 4-alpha-D-{(1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucanosyl}n trehalose to yield trehalose and alpha-(1--gt-4)-D-glucan.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing beta-D-galactose residues in (1--gt-3)-beta-D-galactopyranans.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing beta-D-galactofuranosides, releasing galactose.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of cellobiose from the reducing end of xyloglucans consisting of a beta-(1--gt-4) linked glucan carrying alpha-D-xylosyl groups on O-6 of the glucose residues. To be a substrate, the first residue must be unsubstituted, the second residue may bear a xylosyl group, whether further glycosylated or not, and the third residue, which becomes the new terminus by the action of the enzyme, is preferably xylosylated, but this xylose residue must not be further substituted.
Catalysis of the reaction -  xyloglucan + H2O -eq- xyloglucan oligosaccharides. This reaction is the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in xyloglucan.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-6)-beta-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-N-acetylglucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-N-acetylglucosaminyl sequence of glycoprotein to alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-6)-D-mannose and beta-D-N-acetylglucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-N-acetylglucosaminyl sequences.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing (2--gt-1) linked beta-D-fructofuranose residues in fructans.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing (2--gt-6) linked beta-D-fructofuranose residues in fructans.
Catalysis of the reaction -  xyloglucan + H2O -eq- xyloglucan oligosaccharides. This reaction is the exohydrolysis of 1,4-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in xyloglucan.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of 1,4-beta-D-xylose residues from the reducing end of oligosaccharides.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,4-beta-D-linkages between D-galactose 4-sulfate and 3,6-anhydro-D-galactose-2-sulfate in iota-carrageenans.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,3-alpha-L-galactosidic linkages in agarose, yielding agarotetraose as the major product.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 1,3-alpha-L-galactosidic linkages of neoagaro-oligosaccharides that are smaller than a hexamer, yielding 3,6-anhydro-L-galactose and D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-[beta-D-apiofuranosyl-(1--gt-6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyloxy]isoflavonoid + H2O -eq- a 7-hydroxyisoflavonoid + beta-D-apiofuranosyl-(1--gt-6)-D-glucose.

Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of beta-1,4-linkages in the backbone of lambda-carrageenan, resulting in the tetrasaccharide alpha-D-Galp2,6S2-(1--gt-3)-beta-D-Galp2S-(1--gt-4)-alpha-D-Galp2,6S2-(1--gt-3)-D-Galp2S.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of DNA and polynucleotides, releasing free hypoxanthine.
Catalysis of the cleavage of the N-glycosidic bond between the 5'-pyrimidine residue in cyclobutadipyrimidine (in DNA) and the corresponding deoxy-D-ribose residue.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-methylxanthosine + H(2)O -eq- 7-methylxanthine + H(+) + ribofuranose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-stilbene oxide + H2O -eq- (+)-(1R,2R)-1,2-diphenylethane-1,2-diol.

Catalysis of the reactions -  5,6alpha-epoxy-5alpha-cholestan-3beta-ol + H2O -eq- cholestane-3beta-5alpha,6beta-triol, and 5,6beta-epoxy-5beta-cholestan-3beta-ol + H2O -eq- cholestane-3beta-5alpha,6beta-triol.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of gangliosides and neutral glycosphingolipids, releasing fatty acids to form the lyso-derivatives.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the amide bond in aculeacin A and related neutral lipopeptide antibiotics, releasing the long-chain fatty acid side-chain.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-benzylformamide + H2O -eq- formate + benzylamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (7R)-7-(4-carboxybutanamido)cephalosporanate + H2O -eq- (7R)-7-aminocephalosporanate + glutarate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-(L-gamma-glutamylamino)butanoate + H(2)O -eq- 4-aminobutanoate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-oxo-3-ureidopropanoate + H(2)O -eq- H(+) + malonate + urea.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-hydroxyisourate + H(2)O -eq- 5-hydroxy-2-oxo-4-ureido-2,5-dihydro-1H-imidazole-5-carboxylate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  amidinoproclavaminate + H(2)O -eq- proclavaminate + urea.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dCTP + 2 H(2)O -eq- diphosphate + dUMP + H(+) + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of mixed phospho-anhydride bonds.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-2-haloacid + H2O -eq- (S)-2-hydroxyacid + halide.
Catalysis of the reactions -  (S)-2-haloacid + H2O -eq- (R)-2-hydroxyacid + halide, and (R)-2-haloacid + H2O -eq- (S)-2-hydroxyacid + halide.
Catalysis of the reactions -  (S)-2-haloacid + H2O -eq- (S)-2-hydroxyacid + halide, and (R)-2-haloacid + H2O -eq- (R)-2-hydroxyacid + halide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phosphonopyruvate + H(2)O -eq- phosphate + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phosphonopyruvate + 2 H(+) -eq- CO(2) + phosphonoacetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-dopachrome + H(+) -eq- 5,6-dihydroxyindole + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-dehydro-L-gulonate 6-phosphate + H(+) -eq- L-xylulose 5-phosphate + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-2,4-diaminobutyrate + H(+) -eq- 1,3-diaminopropane + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (1S,2R)-1-C-(indol-3-yl)glycerol 3-phosphate -eq- indole + D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate.
The volume enclosed by the membranes of an acidocalcisome.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,7,4'-trihydroxyisoflavanone -eq- daidzein + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7alpha,12alpha-dihydroxy-3-oxochol-4-en-24-oate -eq- 12alpha-hydroxy-3-oxochola-4,6-dien-24-oate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha,24-tetrahydroxy-5beta-cholestanoyl-CoA -eq- (24E)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholest-24-enoyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N(4)-acetyl-L-2,4-diaminobutyrate -eq- ectoine + H(2)O.

Catalysis of the reactions -  1,5-anhydro-D-fructose -eq- 2-hydroxy-2-(hydroxymethyl)-2H-pyran-3(6H)-one + H2O -  (1a) 1,5-anhydro-D-fructose -eq- 1,5-anhydro-4-deoxy-D-glycero-hex-3-en-2-ulose + H2O and (1b) 1,5-anhydro-4-deoxy-D-glycero-hex-3-en-2-ulose -eq- 2-hydroxy-2-(hydroxymethyl)-2H-pyran-3(6H)-one.
